quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  26,20,"He said, “I did it then while I was one of those astray."
  26,21,"And I fled from you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>when I feared you, then my Lord gave me wise judgment and made me one of the emissaries."
  26,22,"And is that a favor you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>remind me of: that you have enslaved the Children of Israel?”"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said, “And what is the Lord of all realms?”"
  26,24,"He said, “The Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><i class=""s"">(can ever) </i>believe with certitude.”"
  26,25,"He said to those around him, “Are you listening?”"
  26,26,"He said, “Your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers.”"
  26,27,"He said, “This messenger of yours who has been sent to you is certainly a madman.”"
  26,28,"He said, “The Lord of the east and the west and whatever is between them, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>can<i class=""s"">(ever) </i>reason.”"
  26,29,"He said, “If you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>accept any god other than me, I will surely make you of the imprisoned.”"
  26,30,"He said, “What if I bring you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>something evident?”"
  26,31,"He said, “Bring it, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are of the truthful.”"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff and thereupon it was an evident serpent."
  26,33,"And he pulled his hand and thereupon it was white for the beholders."
  26,34,"He said to the chiefs around him, “This is indeed a knowledgeable sorcerer"
  26,35,"who wants to evict you from your land with his sorcery, so what do you command?”"
  26,36,"They said, “Put him off, and his brother, and send summoners to the cities"
  26,37,"to bring you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>every knowledgeable magician.”"
  26,38,"So the sorcerers were assembled for the appointment on a specified day."
  26,39,"And people were told, “Are you going to assemble,"
